<component id="ID_txt11">
<text><![CDATA[<b>Follow the steps for generating a new pair in the ARP table when the destination is on the local network.</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt12">
<text><![CDATA[<b>I need to send a frame to 172.16.0.10 but it outside my network and don't know the MAC address of my gateway (10.10.0.254).</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt13">
<text><![CDATA[<b>If your IP address is 10.10.0.254 please tell 10.10.0.1(00-0d-88-c7-9a).</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt14">
<text><![CDATA[<b>I am 10.10.0.254. So I respond with my MAC address 0060.273A.07BC</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt15">
<text><![CDATA[<b>I need to send a frame to 10.10.0.3 but I don't know the MAC address.</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt16">
<text><![CDATA[<b>If your IP address is 10.10.0.3, please tell 10.10.0.1 (00-0d-88-c7-9a-24).</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt17">
<text><![CDATA[<b>I am 10.10.0.3.<br/>My MAC address is 00-0d-56-09-fb-d1.</b>]]></text>
</component>

<component id="ID_txt18">
<text><![CDATA[<b>I will store 10.10.0.3 and 00-0d-56-09-fb-d1 in my ARP Cache.</b>]]></text>
</component>  

<component id="ID_txt19">
<text><![CDATA[<b>I can now send the frame to 10.10.0.3 with the MAC address 00-0d-56-09-fb-d1.</b>]]></text>
</component>  

